# 🔍 Root Cause Analysis: Schema Drift — Phantom Fields in Production Code

**Date:** 2026-04-08  
**Investigator:** Antigravity (AI Engineering Auditor)  
**Severity:** 🔴 Critical — caused cascading 500 errors in production  
**Affected Systems:** Order Processing, Print Page, Force Process, Cancel Flow

---

## Executive Summary

Three database fields were referenced extensively in `admin-order.service.ts` but **never existed** in `schema.prisma`:

| Phantom Field | Model | Introduced By | Data Spec? | Migration Run? |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `parentOrderId` | `Order` | Story 3.4d | ❌ No data spec | ❌ Never |
| `splitOrders` | `Order` (relation) | Story 3.4d | ❌ No data spec | ❌ Never |
| `netCommission` | `OrderItem` | Story 3.13 | ✅ 3-13-data-spec.md (`3-13-data-spec.md`) | ❌ Never |

This caused `PrismaClientValidationError` → 500 Internal Server Error on every `GET /admin/orders/:id` call and every order status transition involving cancellation.

---

## Detailed Forensic Analysis

### 🔴 Finding 1: `parentOrderId` — False Assumption in Story 3.4d Spec

**Evidence:** story-3.4d-partial-fulfillment.md (`story-3.4d-partial-fulfillment.md`)

> Line 41: *"The schema already has `parentOrderId` `(String?)` and `isForceProcessed` `(Boolean)` on the `Order` model from Phase 1."*

**Reality:** The actual schema.prisma Order model (`schema.prisma`) has **neither field**. The spec author (AI) fabricated the existence of these fields and built the entire implementation plan on a false premise.

**Root Cause:** The AI agent that wrote Story 3.4d **hallucinated** the existence of `parentOrderId` and `isForceProcessed` without verifying against the actual schema file. No human or automated check caught this before the code was generated.

---

### 🔴 Finding 2: `netCommission` — Data Spec Written, Migration Never Executed

**Evidence:** 3-13-data-spec.md (`3-13-data-spec.md`)

> Line 101: *"OrderItem missing requested columns: Need to run Prisma migration for `expectedCommissionAmount`, `discountAbsorbed`, `netCommission`, `commissionRate`, `commissionType`. (Severity: **INFO**)"*

The Data Architect (Kira) correctly identified these fields needed migration. Yet:
1. The migration was **never created** (`prisma migrate dev`)
2. The implementation code in 3-13-commission-checkout-engine.md (`3-13-commission-checkout-engine-and-flexible-pricing.md`) marked it as `[x] done`
3. Code review rounds **never verified** schema parity

**Root Cause:** The workflow lacks a mandatory **"Migration Execution Gate"** — a step that blocks code merge until database schema changes are actually applied and verified.

---

### 🔴 Finding 3: `splitOrders` — Relation Never Defined

The `splitOrders` relation and `parentOrder` back-relation were used in the `getAdminOrderDetail` query but never existed in `schema.prisma`. This is a direct consequence of Finding 1 — since `parentOrderId` was never added, the Prisma relations `splitOrders` and `parentOrder` could never be generated.

